<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-101] Implement trademark designations according to Intel conventions</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-101</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Add an * after Lustre on the title page and as described below&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;From the Legal site page: Proper Use of Other Party Trademarks by Intel (link below):&lt;br/&gt;
&#8226;	Designate other party trademarks with a superscript asterisk &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/emoticons/star_yellow.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;. &lt;br/&gt;
&#8226;	In the first appearance in a headline, and/or the first prominent use&lt;br/&gt;
&#8226;	In the first appearance in the body of text &lt;br/&gt;
&#8226;	The asterisk &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/emoticons/star_yellow.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; may go at the end of the other party&apos;s trademarked name or at the end of the product name.	Examples from the Legal site page: &lt;br/&gt;
&#8226;	Microsoft Windows Vista OS*&lt;br/&gt;
&#8226;	Windows* Vista OS&lt;br/&gt;
&#8226;	HP Pavilion system*&lt;br/&gt;
&#8226;	Adobe Acrobat* software&lt;br/&gt;
These examples show various acceptable formats. The recommended format is an asterisk at the end of the product name, before the noun.&lt;br/&gt;
Use an appropriate noun after the trademark.	On Windows* OS; on Linux* systems&lt;/p&gt;</description>
